President Biden met with Elizabeth Whelan and Cherelle Griner, the loved ones of two American citizens, Paul Whelan and Brittney Griner, who are wrongfully detained in Russia. The President expressed his commitment to working towards bringing them home safely and inquired about the well-being of Elizabeth and Cherelle and their families. The President acknowledged that every minute of their detention is too long. These meetings follow previous discussions with the families to keep them informed about efforts to secure the release of their loved ones. The administration remains dedicated to reuniting them with their families.